# Phase 1: Project & Auth Foundation (Revised with Radix UI)

# Code Style and Structure
- All code in TypeScript with strict mode.
- Use React functional components and Hooks only.
- Organize auth code in `src/features/auth`.
- Use Radix UI components for all base UI elements (buttons, dialogs, inputs, toasts):
  - Import from `@radix-ui/react-<component>` packages.
  - Wrap Radix primitives in local `src/components/ui/` wrappers to apply Tailwind theming.
  - Prefer Radix’s accessible primitives over custom HTML elements.

# Project Configuration
- use yarn package manager
- Absolute imports from `src/`.
- Tailwind CSS configured in `tailwind.config.js`.
- Firebase initialized in `src/lib/firebase.ts` (Auth, Firestore, Storage).
- Add Radix UI peer dependencies and set up any required CSS resets (e.g., include `@radix-ui/react-toast/styles.css`).

# TypeScript Usage
- Prefer interfaces; avoid `any`.
- Explicit return types on all exported functions.
- For Radix components, type any extended props using `ComponentProps<typeof RadixComponent>`.

# Syntax & Formatting
- Enforce Prettier via husky pre-commit.
- ESLint (Airbnb + TS); CI fails on warnings.
- Commit messages follow Conventional Commits.

# Firebase Integration
- Implement AuthProvider + `useAuth` hook with Firebase Auth.
- No Firestore reads/writes until Phase 2.

# CI/CD
- GitHub Actions pipeline:
  1. Install dependencies  
  2. Run ESLint → fail on warnings  
  3. Build app (`npm run build`)

# Testing
- Add at least one Jest test for AuthProvider.
- Add component tests for Radix wrappers (e.g., button, dialog) using React Testing Library.
